CONFIGURATION

Once you have deployed these files to a web server, you will need to set the following environment variables
in the virtual host configuration:

#Database Connection Settings
SetEnv PF_DB_USERNAME "{DB Username}"
SetEnv PF_DB_PASSWORD "{DB Password}"
SetEnv PF_DB_HOST "{DB Host}"
SetEnv PF_DB_NAME "{DB Name}"

#Facebook Account
SetEnv PF_FACEBOOK_APP_ID "{Facebook App ID}"

#Yummly API
SetEnv PF_YUMMLY_URL "http://api.yummly.com/v1/api/"
SetEnv PF_YUMMLY_APP_ID "{Yummly App ID}"
SetEnv PF_YUMMLY_APP_KEY "{Yummly App Key}"

#Google Analytics Account
SetEnv PF_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ACCOUNT "{Google Analytics Account}"

#Feedback Widget Company
SetEnv PF_FEEDBACK_COMPANY "{Feedback widget company name}"

#Site location on server
SetEnv PF_INSTALL_PATH "/var/www/www.somdomain.org"

#Location of static assets (ex: a CDN)
SetEnv PF_BASE_URL "http://assets.somdomain.org/stage/"
SetEnv PF_SITE_URL "http://www.somdomain.org/"

#Log file settings
SetEnv PF_LOG_PATH "/etc/httpd/logs/www.somdomain.org"
SetEnv PF_LOG_FILENAME "php_error.log"
SetEnv PF_LOG_EMAIL "rick@somedomain.org"

#Import script credentials
SetEnv PF_IMPORT_USERNAME "ImportUser"
SetEnv PF_IMPORT_PASSWORD "ImportPass"